# WiFi Tariff Management Service - API Tests
# Complete test suite for CRUD operations and error handling

### =============================================================================
### BASIC CRUD OPERATIONS (Happy Path)
### =============================================================================

### 1. Get all tariffs (should be empty initially)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs

### 2. Create new tariff (basic test)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Premium Business WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### 3. Get tariff by ID (use ID from step 2 response)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/1

### 4. Create second tariff for testing
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Basic Guest WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 25,
  "uploadMbps": 10,
  "durationHours": 2,
  "maxDevices": 2,
  "basePrice": 4.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### 5. Get all tariffs (should now show multiple)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs

### 6. Update first tariff
PUT {{host}}/api/tariffs/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Updated Premium WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 150,
  "uploadMbps": 75,
  "durationHours": 48,
  "maxDevices": 8,
  "basePrice": 29.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "MONTHLY"
}

### 7. Verify update worked
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/1

### 8. Delete second tariff
DELETE {{host}}/api/tariffs/2

### 9. Verify deletion (should return 404)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/2

### =============================================================================
### ERROR HANDLING TESTS - Path Parameters
### =============================================================================

### E1. Invalid ID type (string instead of integer)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/abc

### E2. Negative ID
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/-1

### E3. Zero ID
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/0

### E4. Non-existent ID (resource not found)
GET {{host}}/api/tariffs/999

### E5. DELETE with invalid ID type
DELETE {{host}}/api/tariffs/invalid

### E6. DELETE with negative ID
DELETE {{host}}/api/tariffs/-5

### =============================================================================
### ERROR HANDLING TESTS - Request Body Validation
### =============================================================================

### E7. Missing required fields
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50
}

### E8. Invalid data type (string for number)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": "not-a-number",
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E9. Constraint violation (negative price)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Price WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": -10.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E10. Empty string name (should fail @NotBlank)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E11. Name too short (should fail @Size)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "AB",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E12. Multiple constraint violations
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "downloadMbps": -1,
  "uploadMbps": 0,
  "durationHours": -5,
  "maxDevices": 0,
  "basePrice": -100.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E13. Completely empty request body
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### =============================================================================
### ERROR HANDLING TESTS - Validation Groups (POST vs PUT)
### =============================================================================

### E14. POST with ID provided (should be rejected - Create group)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 5,
  "name": "Test WiFi with ID",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E15. POST with null ID (should work)
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": null,
  "name": "Test WiFi with null ID",
  "downloadMbps": 100,
  "uploadMbps": 50,
  "durationHours": 24,
  "maxDevices": 5,
  "basePrice": 19.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E16. PUT without ID in body (should be rejected - Update group)
PUT {{host}}/api/tariffs/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Premium WiFi",
  "downloadMbps": 150,
  "uploadMbps": 75,
  "durationHours": 48,
  "maxDevices": 8,
  "basePrice": 29.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### E17. PUT with ID mismatch (URL vs body - uses id in url - to check business requirements)
PUT {{host}}/api/tariffs/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999,
  "name": "Mismatched ID Test",
  "downloadMbps": 150,
  "uploadMbps": 75,
  "durationHours": 48,
  "maxDevices": 8,
  "basePrice": 29.99,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### =============================================================================
### BOUNDARY TESTING
### =============================================================================

### B1. Minimum valid values
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Min",
  "downloadMbps": 1,
  "uploadMbps": 1,
  "durationHours": 1,
  "maxDevices": 1,
  "basePrice": 0.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "billingType": "ONE_TIME"
}

### B2. Large valid values
POST {{host}}/api/tariffs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Maximum Speed Enterprise WiFi Package with Extended Duration",
  "downloadMbps": 5000,
  "uploadMbps": 2500,
  "durationHours": 720,
  "maxDevices": 100,
  "basePrice": 999.99,
  "currency": "USD",
  "billingType": "MONTHLY"
}

